<paragraph id="AE754931FFDDAC5311CDF40BFC53F8FB" blockId="11.[145,761,1425,1876]" lastBlockId="11.[809,1425,1425,1876]" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">
For all of these reasons, MNHNL TU885 is clearly assignable to 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDDAC53105FF415FDA0F89C" baseAuthorityName="Maisch" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[315,543,1823,1844]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC53105FF415FDA0F89C" box="[315,543,1823,1844]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">Temnodontosaurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The skull roof of MNHNL TU885 shares many similarities with that of 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDDAC531223F69BFC54FA0E" authorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[839,1003,1425,1446]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zetlandicus">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC531223F69BFC54FA0E" box="[839,1003,1425,1446]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">T. zetlandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="36F155B4FFDDAC531299F69BFBFFFA0E" box="[1021,1088,1425,1447]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[163,241,1052,1074]" captionTargetBox="[166,1446,198,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-457@12.[163,1449,195,1012]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Braincase comparison of the holotype of Temnodontosaurus zetlandicus comb. nov. (CAMSM J35176) (A) and the referred specimen of Temnodontosaurus cf. zetlandicus (MNHNL TU885) (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536812/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), such as: (1) the bifurcated posterior processes of the nasal which partially covers the postfrontal which anteriorly appears in the medial and anterolateral processes; (2) the presence of a prominent mediolaterally oriented ridge on the postfrontal which forms the anterior margin of the supratemporal fenestra; and (3) a lanceolate frontal posteriorly covered by a slender forked process of the parietal. The skull roof of MNHNL TU885 also resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDDAC531295F5AFFB39F912" baseAuthorityName="Maisch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[1009,1158,1701,1722]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigonodon">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC531295F5AFFB39F912" box="[1009,1158,1701,1722]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">T. trigonodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the presence of the bifurcated posterior processes of the nasal markedly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDDAC5312D8F5E9FAA1F95F" authority="(Maisch, 1998 b)" baseAuthorityName="Maisch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[956,1310,1762,1784]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigonodon">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC5312D8F5E9FBE7F95F" box="[956,1112,1762,1784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">T. trigonodon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CA5B34C0FFDDAC53150EF5E8FAACF950" author="Maisch MW" box="[1130,1299,1762,1784]" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" pagination="401 - 431" refId="ref13373" refString="Maisch MW. 1998 b. Short review of the ichthyosaurs of the Posidonienschiefer with remarks on the taxonomy of the Stenopterygiidae and Temnodontosauridae. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Abhandlungen 209: 401 - 431." type="journal article" year="1998">Maisch, 1998b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. MNHNL TU885 is also similar in size and in cranial proportions to 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDDAC531221F42AFC5FF89C" authorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[837,992,1823,1845]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zetlandicus">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC531221F42AFC5FF89C" box="[837,992,1823,1845]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">T. zetlandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<tableCitation id="E3487C8AFFDDAC531573F415FBD6F89C" box="[1047,1129,1823,1845]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="13.[143,207,196,217]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Table 1. Measurements (anteroposterior length," httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/FAB519B9FFDBAC5511EBF3CEFEF6FEE7" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" tableUuid="FAB519B9FFDBAC5511EBF3CEFEF6FEE7">Table 1</tableCitation>
) and is here referred to as 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDDAC53124DF435FC5AF8FB" authorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[809,997,1854,1876]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="11" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zetlandicus">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC53124DF435FC80F8FC" box="[809,831,1855,1876]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">T.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDDAC531200F434FC5AF8FB" box="[868,997,1854,1875]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="183">zetlandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="FAB519B9FFDAAC5411C7F716FC76FBE7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536812" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6536812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536812/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="184" startId="12.[163,241,1052,1074]" targetBox="[166,1446,198,1009]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="AE754931FFDAAC5411C7F716FC76FBE7" blockId="12.[163,1443,1052,1103]" pageId="12" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDAAC5411C7F716FEB4FB99" bold="true" box="[163,267,1052,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="184">Figure 7.</emphasis>
Braincase comparison of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDAAC5413DCF716FC44FB9A" authorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[696,1019,1052,1074]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="12" pageNumber="184" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zetlandicus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDAAC5413DCF716FC44FB9A" box="[696,1019,1052,1074]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="184">Temnodontosaurus zetlandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="878D2858FFDAAC541564F716FBD5FB9A" box="[1024,1130,1052,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="184" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(CAMSM J35176) (A) and the referred specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="69CA32B2FFDAAC54101BF733FD61FBE7" authorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Laboury &amp; Bennion &amp; Thuy &amp; Weis &amp; Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[383,734,1081,1103]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptopterygiidae" genus="Temnodontosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ichthyosauria" pageId="12" pageNumber="184" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zetlandicus">
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDAAC54101BF733FDFAFBE7" box="[383,581,1081,1103]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="184">Temnodontosaurus</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="9CBE9523FFDAAC54130CF733FD61FBE7" box="[616,734,1081,1103]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="184">zetlandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MNHNL TU885) (B).
</paragraph>
</caption>
